question: 日欧
sourceMnemonic: The <ja>日</ja> refers to <kanji>Japan</kanji> (It's the <ja>日</ja> of <ja>日本</ja>). So, you have Japan and <kanji>Europe</kanji>, which is <vocabulary>Japan and Europe</vocabulary> or <vocabulary>Europe and Japan</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
